The union of sets A and B, denoted as A ∪ B, is the set of all elements that are in either set A or set B or in both. In this case, the union is:

A ∪ B = {2, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16}

The intersection of sets A and B, denoted as A ∩ B, is the set of all elements that are common to both set A and set B. In this case, the intersection is:

A ∩ B = {4, 8}
